<?xml version='1.0'?>
<!DOCTYPE book PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DocBook XML V4.5//EN" 
    "http://www.oasis-open.org/docbook/xml/4.5/docbookx.dtd">
<book id="ejb-intro">
    <bookinfo>
        <title>Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) Overview</title>
        <subtitle></subtitle>
        <issuenum>${content.version}</issuenum>
        <pubdate>${docbook.pubdate}</pubdate>
        <copyright>
            <year>${copyright.year}</year>
            <holder>${copyright.holder}</holder>
        </copyright>
        <abstract>
            <para>This presentation provides an introduction to enterprise development
                using the server-side Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) standard. 
            </para>
        </abstract>
        
    </bookinfo>

    <preface id="ejb-intro-purpose">
        <title>Purpose</title>
        <section id="ejb-intro-goals">
            <title>Goals</title>
            <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                <listitem><para>Introduce the purpose of an EJB (why?)</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>Introduce the different EJB styles</para>
                    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                        <listitem><para>Stateless EJB</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Stateful EJB</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Singleton EJB</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Message Driven EJB</para></listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </listitem>
                <listitem><para>Introduce different EJB interface options</para>
                    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                        <listitem><para>Remote</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Local</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>No Interface (Local)</para></listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </listitem>
                <listitem><para>Introduce different deployment options for EJBs</para>
                    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                        <listitem><para>Naked EJB Archive (JAR)</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Enterprise Archive (EAR)</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Web Archive (WAR)</para></listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </listitem>
                <listitem><para>Develop, deploy, and test a simple Stateless EJB</para></listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>

        <section id="ejb-intro-objectives">
            <title>Objectives</title>
            <para>At the completion of this topic, the student shall be able to:</para>
            <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                <listitem><para>State reasons for/against adding an EJB to a JavaEE application</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>State the four different types of EJBs and reasons for/against using each</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>State the three different built-in interface types and when to/not-to use each</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>State the three different deployment options and when to/not-to use each</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>Develop, deploy, and test a simple Stateless EJB</para>
                    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                        <listitem><para>EJB (without resource requirements)</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Remote interface</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Naked EJB deployment</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Integration test (IT)</para></listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>
    </preface>


